## 🔹 **4. Use `vector` Instead of `array`**
```cpp
vector<int> v(n);  // Instead of int arr[n];
v.push_back(10);   // Dynamic resizing
```
✅ **Effect**: No need to manage memory manually.

**Preallocating Space for Speed**
```cpp
vector<int> v;
v.reserve(1e6);  // Preallocates space to avoid frequent resizing
```

---

## 🔹 **5. Sorting and Searching Faster**
Sorting in `O(n log n)`:
```cpp
sort(v.begin(), v.end());  // Sort in ascending order
sort(v.rbegin(), v.rend());  // Sort in descending order
```
Binary search using `lower_bound` and `upper_bound`:
```cpp
auto it = lower_bound(v.begin(), v.end(), value);
int pos = it - v.begin();
```
✅ **Effect**: Faster than writing custom sorting or binary search.

